<section id="projects">

<span class="section-tag">
PROJECTS
</span>

<h2>
Major Projects
</h2>

<div class="project-grid">

<div class="project">

<img src="/images/poe/topgear.jpg">

<h3>⚙️ Top Gear</h3>

<p>

Using only gear ratios, our challenge was to build the slowest robot possible while still making it move.

</p>

</div>

<div class="project">

<img src="/images/poe/sillywalks.jpg">

<h3>Silly Walks</h3>

<p>

Designing a robot that could move without using wheels forced us to think creatively about motion.

</p>

</div>

<div class="project">

<img src="/images/poe/goingdistance.jpg">

<h3>Going the Distance</h3>

<p>

One of our first programming projects where we learned autonomous movement and control.

</p>

</div>

<div class="project">

<img src="/images/poe/biomimicry.jpg">

<h3>BioMimicry ⭐</h3>

<p>

My favorite project. We designed a robot inspired by an animal using sensors and programming. It was also the hardest project because it combined everything we had learned throughout the course.

</p>

</div>

<div class="project">

<img src="/images/poe/assistiverobot.jpg">

<h3>PV PE Assistive Robotic Systems</h3>

<p>

A final engineering challenge focused on designing robotic solutions that could assist people in everyday life.

</p>

</div>

