<section id="reflection" class="reflection">

<span class="section-tag">
FINAL REFLECTION
</span>

<h2>
What I Learned
</h2>

<div class="reflection-card">

<h3>
BioMimicry Was My Favorite Project
</h3>

<p>

BioMimicry challenged me more than any other project because it combined programming, sensors, engineering design, testing, and teamwork into one solution. It pushed me to think beyond simply making something work—I had to understand why it worked.

</p>

<div class="reflection-grid">

<div class="reflection-box">

<h4>Biggest Lesson</h4>

<p>

Teamwork only works when communication comes first.

</p>

</div>

<div class="reflection-box">

<h4>Favorite Project</h4>

<p>

BioMimicry

</p>

</div>

<div class="reflection-box">

<h4>Biggest Challenge</h4>

<p>

Programming robots that combined multiple sensors while working effectively as a team.

</p>

</div>

<div class="reflection-box">

<h4>Looking Back</h4>

<p>

Being consistently ahead in the class gave me the opportunity to experiment, improve my code, and help classmates. It helped build the confidence I now have when approaching programming and robotics.

</p>

